OL,3,COldest French restaurant in London
OL,4,Cauctions off decor
OL,6,FLondon's oldest family-run French
OL,7,Frestaurant is auctioning off its
OL,8,Fclassic interior decorations to make
OL,9,Fway for a new look.
OL,11,FOn a busy street in Covent Garden,
OL,12,Fusually adorned with a large tricolour
OL,13,Fflag, Mon Plaisir has served up "great
OL,14,Ffood" and "rude" waitstaff for more
OL,15,Fthan 80 years.
OL,17,FThe bistro was founded in 1943 during
OL,18,Fthe Second World War by two brothers,
OL,19,Fbefore being sold to their maitre'd
OL,20,FAlain Lhermitte in 1973.
